---
title: Git Add
---
## Git Add

The `git add` Add file contents to the index.  There are a number of different options for this command that won't be covered here, but you can take a look at all of them in the <a href='https://git-scm.com/docs/git-add' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>Git documentation</a>.

### Add an Existing File
To add an existing file, run the command:
```shell
git add FILE-NAME
```

### Checking before adding
To check files you'll want to add, run the commande:
```shell
git status
```
or:
```shell
g status
```

### Add all Existing Files
To add all files in one command line, run the command:
```shell
git add -A
```
The `-A` stands for All and for no-ignore-removal
